cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.DS

This paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques for the segmentation of skin lesions in dermoscopy images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of fuzzy classification and histogram thresholding, which are common techniques in information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) domains. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques, which are also relevant to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
